(ii) Determine the maximum possible weight of the platform and engineer, $W$, so that the system does not topple. [3]
(iii) A sign placed on the platform gives the warning: "Maximum 2 persons or 200 kg". Consider whether or not this is a reasonable warning to give. The weight of the platform is 1700 N. [4]

**Answer:**
(a) The moment is the force multiplied by the perpendicular distance from the pivot to the line of action of the force. (Options A, C, and E would be the correct geometric representations).
(b)(i) The horizontal distance is $x = 6 \cos 25^\circ = 5.44 \approx 5.4$ m.
(b)(ii) Taking moments about the pivot: Anti-clockwise = Clockwise.
$2.2 \times 10^4 \times 2.00 = W \times 5.44 + (3.0 \times 10^3 \times 3.44)$
