### Question 9
**Question:**
A simplified energy level diagram for a three-level laser has levels: G = 0 eV, U = 1.79 eV, P = 2.25 eV.
(a)(i) Explain what is meant by stimulated emission involving levels U and G. [2]
(ii) State why there must be more electrons in U than in G for light amplification to occur. [1]
