(c)(iii) Momentum per second hitting the surface = $(2.1 \times 10^{18}) \times (9.6 \times 10^{-28}) = 2.0 \times 10^{-9}$ N. Force on the reflecting surface (since light is reflected perfectly, the change in momentum is doubled) = $2 \times 2.0 \times 10^{-9} = 4.0 \times 10^{-9}$ N.
